WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.840
Part 5 of The Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde.

00:21.320 --> 00:24.380
Henry Jekyll's Full Statement of the Case

00:27.160 --> 00:36.320
I was born to a large fortune, endowed besides with excellent parts, inclined by nature to

00:36.320 --> 00:42.740
industry, fond of the respect of the wise and good among my fellow men, and thus as

00:42.740 --> 00:48.900
might have been supposed, with every guarantee of an honorable and distinguished future.

00:48.900 --> 00:57.340
And indeed the worst of my faults was a certain impatient gaiety of disposition, such as has

00:57.340 --> 01:04.200
made the happiness of many, but such as I found it hard to reconcile with my imperious

01:04.200 --> 01:10.380
desire to carry my head high and wear a more than commonly grave countenance before the

01:10.380 --> 01:10.820
public.

01:12.080 --> 01:19.180
Hence it came about that I concealed my pleasures, and that when I reached years of reflection,

01:19.620 --> 01:24.320
and began to look round me and take stock of my progress and position in the world,

01:24.940 --> 01:30.700
I stood already committed to a profound duplicity of me.

01:32.000 --> 01:38.960
Many a man would have even blazoned such irregularities as I was guilty of, but from the high views

01:38.960 --> 01:46.080
that I had set before me, I regarded and hid them with an almost morbid sense of shame.

01:47.160 --> 01:53.760
It was thus rather the exacting nature of my aspirations, than any particular degradation

01:53.760 --> 02:00.840
in my faults, that made me what I was, and with an even deeper trench than in the majority

02:00.840 --> 02:08.300
of men, severed in me those provinces of good and ill which divide and compound man's dual

02:08.300 --> 02:08.820
nature.

02:10.100 --> 02:17.320
In this case, I was driven to reflect deeply and inveterate on that hard law of life which

02:17.320 --> 02:23.540
lies at the root of religion, and is one of the most plentiful springs of distress.

02:24.660 --> 02:29.560
Though so profound a double-dealer, I was in no sense a hypocrite.

02:29.960 --> 02:32.740
Both sides of me were in dead earnest.

02:33.520 --> 02:40.340
I was no more myself when I laid aside restraint and plunged in shame, than when I laboured

02:40.340 --> 02:46.240
in the eye of the day at the furtherance of knowledge or the relief of sorrow and suffering.

02:47.580 --> 02:54.160
And it chanced that the direction of my scientific studies, which led wholly towards the mystic

02:54.160 --> 03:00.440
and the transcendental, reacted and shed a strong light on this consciousness of the

03:00.440 --> 03:02.660
war among my members.

03:03.780 --> 03:10.020
With every day, and from both sides of my intelligence, the moral and the intellectual,

03:10.560 --> 03:17.820
I thus drew steadily nearer to that truth by whose partial discovery I have been doomed

03:17.820 --> 03:26.080
to such a dreadful shipwreck, that man is not truly one, but truly two.

03:26.860 --> 03:33.060
I say two, because the state of my own knowledge does not pass beyond that point.

03:34.380 --> 03:40.900
Others will follow, others will outstrip me on the same lines, and I hazard the guess

03:40.900 --> 03:48.740
that man will be ultimately known for a mere polity of multifarious, incongruous, and independent

03:48.740 --> 03:49.480
denizens.

03:49.480 --> 03:58.780
I, for my part, from the nature of my life, advanced infallibly in one direction, and

03:58.780 --> 04:00.360
in one direction only.

04:01.120 --> 04:08.440
It was on the moral side, and in my own person, that I learned to recognize the thorough and

04:08.440 --> 04:10.680
primitive duality of man.

04:11.420 --> 04:17.780
I saw that, of the two natures that contended in the field of my consciousness, even if

04:17.780 --> 04:24.660
I could rightly be said to be either, it was only because I was radically both, and

04:24.660 --> 04:30.440
from an early date, even before the course of my scientific discoveries had begun to

04:30.440 --> 04:37.300
suggest the most naked possibility of such a miracle, I had learned to dwell with pleasure,

04:37.700 --> 04:43.120
as a beloved daydream, on the thought of the separation of these elements.

04:43.860 --> 04:51.620
If each, I told myself, could be housed in separate identities, life would be relieved

04:51.620 --> 04:57.900
of all that was unbearable, the unjust might go his way, delivered from the aspirations

04:57.900 --> 05:04.620
and remorse of his more upright twin, and the just could walk steadfastly and securely

05:04.620 --> 05:11.360
on his upward path, doing the good things in which he found his pleasure, and no longer

05:11.360 --> 05:16.980
exposed to disgrace and penitence by the hands of this extraneous evil.

05:18.060 --> 05:25.560
It was the course of mankind that these incongruous faggots were thus bound together, that in

05:25.560 --> 05:32.160
the agonized womb of consciousness these polar twins should be continuously struggling.

05:33.280 --> 05:36.320
How then were they disassociated?

05:37.020 --> 05:44.660
I was so far in my reflections, when, as I have said, a side-light began to shine upon

05:44.660 --> 05:46.960
the subject from the laboratory table.

05:47.960 --> 05:55.440
I began to perceive more deeply than it has ever yet been stated the trembling immateriality,

05:55.720 --> 06:02.780
the mist-like transience, of this seemingly so solid body in which we walk attired.

06:03.600 --> 06:10.220
Certain agents I found to have the power to shake and pluck back that fleshly vestment,

06:10.780 --> 06:13.760
even as a wind might toss the curtains of a pavilion.

06:14.940 --> 06:21.840
For two good reasons I will not enter deeply into this scientific branch of my confession.

06:22.540 --> 06:28.900
First, because I have been made to learn that the doom and burden of our life is bound forever

06:28.900 --> 06:35.960
on man's shoulders, and when the attempt is made to cast it off, it but returns upon us

06:35.960 --> 06:39.040
with more unfamiliar and more awful pressure.

06:40.160 --> 06:48.820
Second, because as my narrative will make, alas, too evident, my discoveries were incomplete.

06:50.280 --> 06:57.140
Enough then that I not only recognized my natural body from the mere aura and effulgence

06:57.140 --> 07:04.700
of certain of the powers that made up my spirit, but managed to compound a drug by which these

07:04.700 --> 07:11.300
powers should be dethroned from their supremacy, and a second form and countenance substituted,

07:11.980 --> 07:18.360
none the less natural to me, because they were the expression and bore the stamp of

07:18.360 --> 07:20.480
lower elements in my soul.

07:21.480 --> 07:25.980
I hesitated long before I put this theory to the test of practice.

07:26.780 --> 07:34.680
I knew well that I risked death, for any drug that so potently controlled and shook the

07:34.680 --> 07:42.460
very fortress of identity might by the least scruple of an overdose, or at the least inopportunity

07:42.460 --> 07:48.900
in the moment of exhibition, utterly blot out that immaterial tabernacle which I looked

07:48.900 --> 07:50.260
to it to change.

07:51.160 --> 07:58.880
But the temptation of a discovery so singular and profound at last overcame the suggestions

07:58.880 --> 07:59.720
of alarm.

08:01.120 --> 08:03.900
I had long since prepared my tincture.

08:04.500 --> 08:10.960
I purchased at once, from a firm of wholesale chemists, a large quantity of a particular

08:10.960 --> 08:18.720
salt which I knew from my experiments to be the last ingredient required, and late one

08:18.720 --> 08:25.400
accursed night I compounded the elements, watched them boil and smoke together in the

08:25.400 --> 08:33.700
glass, and when the ebullition had subsided, with a strong glow of courage, drank off the

08:33.700 --> 08:34.100
potion.

08:35.720 --> 08:39.020
The most racking pangs succeeded.

08:40.100 --> 08:47.540
A grinding in the bones, deadly nausea, and a horror of the spirit that cannot be exceeded

08:47.540 --> 08:49.740
at the hour of birth or death.

08:51.120 --> 08:59.220
Then these agonies began swiftly to subside, and I came to myself as if out of a great

08:59.220 --> 08:59.900
sickness.

09:00.840 --> 09:07.400
There was something strange in my sensations, something indescribably new, and from its

09:07.400 --> 09:10.180
varied novelty incredibly sweet.

09:11.060 --> 09:14.760
I felt younger, lighter, happier in body.

09:15.320 --> 09:21.940
Within I was conscious of a heady recklessness, a current of disordered sensual images running

09:21.940 --> 09:29.960
like a mill-race in my fancy, a solution of the bonds of obligation, an unknown but not

09:29.960 --> 09:32.360
an innocent freedom of the soul.

09:33.660 --> 09:41.660
I knew myself, at the first breath of this new life, to be more wicked, tenfold more

09:41.660 --> 09:49.300
wicked, sold a slave to my original evil, and the thought in that moment braced and

09:49.300 --> 09:50.940
delighted me like wine.

09:51.920 --> 09:59.000
I stretched out my hands, exulting in the freshness of these sensations, and in the

09:59.000 --> 10:03.940
act I was suddenly aware that I had lost in stature.

10:04.960 --> 10:07.860
There was no mirror at that date in my room.

10:08.230 --> 10:13.700
That which stands beside me as I write was brought there later on, and for the very purpose

10:13.700 --> 10:15.080
of these transformations.

10:16.240 --> 10:19.860
The night, however, was far gone into the morning.

10:20.380 --> 10:25.600
The morning, black as it was, was nearly ripe for the conception of the day.

10:26.120 --> 10:32.740
The inmates of my house were locked in the most rigorous hours of slumber, and I determined,

10:32.740 --> 10:39.780
flush as I was with hope and triumph, to venture in my new shape as far as to my bedroom.

10:40.520 --> 10:46.480
I crossed the yard, wherein the constellations looked down upon me, I could have thought

10:46.480 --> 10:53.520
with wonder, the first creature of that sort that their unsleeping vigilance had yet disclosed

10:53.520 --> 10:54.020
to them.

10:54.580 --> 11:01.480
I stole through the corridors, a stranger in my own house, and coming to my room, I

11:01.480 --> 11:06.920
saw for the first time the appearance of Edward Hyde.

11:08.480 --> 11:15.620
I must here speak by theory alone, saying not that which I know, but that which I suppose

11:15.620 --> 11:17.040
to be most probable.

11:18.460 --> 11:25.240
The evil side of my nature, to which I had now transferred the stamping efficacy, was

11:25.240 --> 11:30.440
less robust and less developed than the good which I had just deposed.

11:31.260 --> 11:37.380
Again, in the course of my life, which had been, after all, nine-tenths a life of effort,

11:37.580 --> 11:44.820
virtue and control, it had been much less exercise and much less exhausted, and hence,

11:44.960 --> 11:51.580
as I think, it came about that Edward Hyde was so much smaller, slighter, and younger

11:51.580 --> 11:53.460
than Henry Jekyll.

11:53.460 --> 12:00.260
Even as good shone upon the countenance of the one, evil was written broadly and plainly

12:00.260 --> 12:01.620
on the face of the other.

12:02.740 --> 12:09.280
Evil besides, which I must still believe to be the lethal side of man, had left on that

12:09.280 --> 12:13.020
body an imprint of deformity and decay.

12:13.840 --> 12:21.520
And yet, when I looked upon that ugly idol in the glass, I was conscious of no repugnance,

12:21.520 --> 12:23.840
rather of a leap of welcome.

12:24.820 --> 12:26.960
This too was myself.

12:27.540 --> 12:29.800
It seemed natural and human.

12:30.340 --> 12:34.680
In my eyes it bore a livelier image of the spirit.

12:35.200 --> 12:41.640
It seemed more express and single than the imperfect and divided countenance I had been

12:41.640 --> 12:43.620
hitherto accustomed to call mine.

12:44.580 --> 12:50.160
And in so far as I was doubtless right, I have observed that when I wore the semblance

12:50.160 --> 12:56.980
of Edward Hyde, none could come near to me at first without a visible misgiving of the

12:56.980 --> 12:57.340
flesh.

12:58.440 --> 13:05.800
This, I take it, was because all human beings, as we meet them, are co-mingled out of good

13:05.800 --> 13:13.620
and evil, and Edward Hyde, alone in the ranks of mankind, was pure evil.

13:15.300 --> 13:17.920
I lingered but a moment at the mirror.

13:18.480 --> 13:21.660
The second and conclusive experiment had yet to be attempted.

13:22.280 --> 13:28.580
It yet remained to be seen if I had lost my identity beyond redemption, and must flee

13:28.580 --> 13:32.380
before daylight from a house that was no longer mine.

13:33.480 --> 13:39.900
And hurrying back to my cabinet, I once more prepared and drank the cup, once more suffered

13:39.900 --> 13:47.240
the pangs of disillusion, and came to myself once more with the character, the stature,

13:47.440 --> 13:49.980
and the face of Henry Jackall.

13:51.240 --> 13:54.920
That night I had come to the fatal crossroads.

13:55.940 --> 14:02.300
Had I approached my discovery in a more noble spirit, had I risked the experiment while

14:02.300 --> 14:09.600
under the empire of generous or pious aspirations, all must have been otherwise, and from these

14:09.880 --> 14:15.060
agonies of death and birth I had come forth an angel instead of a fiend.

14:15.980 --> 14:19.000
The drug had no discriminating action.

14:19.420 --> 14:22.480
It was neither diabolical nor divine.

14:23.300 --> 14:27.680
It but shook the doors of the prison-house of my disposition.

14:28.860 --> 14:35.460
And like the captives of Philippi, that which stood within ran forth.

14:35.460 --> 14:40.220
At that time my virtue slumbered.

14:40.480 --> 14:47.600
My evil, kept awake by ambition, was alert and swift to seize the occasion, and the thing

14:47.600 --> 14:50.540
that was projected was Edward Hyde.

14:51.220 --> 14:59.120
Hence, although I had now two characters as well as two appearances, one was wholly evil,

14:59.280 --> 15:06.600
and the other was still the old Henry Jackall, that incongruous compound of whose reformation

15:06.600 --> 15:10.200
and improvement I had already learned to despair.

15:11.500 --> 15:15.580
The movement was thus wholly toward the worse.

15:17.460 --> 15:23.380
Even at that time I had not conquered my aversions to the dryness of a life of study.

15:24.100 --> 15:29.820
I would still be merrily disposed at times, and as my pleasures were, to say the least,

15:30.040 --> 15:35.700
dignified, and I was not only well-known and highly considered, but growing towards the

15:35.700 --> 15:41.760
elderly man, this incoherency of my life was daily growing more unwelcome.

15:42.800 --> 15:49.020
It was on this side that my new power tempted me, until I fell in slavery.

15:49.740 --> 15:57.420
I had but to drink the cup to doff at once the body of the noted professor, and to assume,

15:57.640 --> 16:01.020
like a thick cloak, that of Edward Hyde.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.700
I smiled at the notion.

16:04.020 --> 16:10.640
It seemed to me at the time to be humorous, and I made my preparations with the most studious

16:10.640 --> 16:11.100
care.

16:11.980 --> 16:17.940
I took and furnished that house in Soho to which Hyde was tracked by the police, and

16:17.940 --> 16:24.220
engaged as a housekeeper a creature whom I knew well to be silent and unscrupulous.

16:25.160 --> 16:32.060
On the other side I announced to my servants that a Mr. Hyde, whom I described, was to

16:32.060 --> 16:38.940
have full liberty and power about my house in the square, and to parry mishaps I even

16:38.940 --> 16:43.340
called and made myself a familiar object in my second character.

16:44.140 --> 16:51.320
I next drew up that will to which you so much objected, so that if anything befell me in

16:51.320 --> 16:57.480
the person of Dr. Jekyll, I could enter on that of Edward Hyde without pecuniary loss,

16:58.400 --> 17:06.900
and thus fortified, as I supposed, on every side, I began to profit by the strange immunities

17:06.900 --> 17:08.180
of my position.

17:09.100 --> 17:15.920
Men have before hired bravos to transact their crimes, while their own person in reputation

17:15.920 --> 17:17.400
sat under shelter.

17:18.460 --> 17:22.220
I was the first that ever did so for his pleasures.

17:22.960 --> 17:29.060
I was the first that could plod in the public eye with a load of genial respectability,

17:29.580 --> 17:36.520
and in a moment, like a schoolboy, strip off these lendings and spring headlong into the

17:36.520 --> 17:37.500
sea of liberty.

17:38.460 --> 17:44.240
But for me, in my impenetrable mantle, the safety was complete.

17:44.980 --> 17:47.620
Think of it, I did not even exist.

17:48.440 --> 17:54.480
Let me but escape into my laboratory door, give me but a second or two to mix and swallow

17:54.480 --> 18:00.960
the draught that I had always standing ready, and whatever he had done, Edward Hyde would

18:00.960 --> 18:08.800
away like the stain of breath upon a mirror, and there in his stead, quietly at home, trimming

18:08.800 --> 18:15.700
the midnight lamp in his study, a man who could afford to laugh at suspicion would be

18:15.700 --> 18:17.140
Henry Jekyll.

18:19.300 --> 18:27.120
The pleasures which I made haste to seek in my disguise were, as I have said, undignified.

18:27.560 --> 18:34.820
I would scarce use a harder term, but in the hands of Edward Hyde they soon began to turn

18:34.820 --> 18:36.340
toward the monstrous.

18:36.840 --> 18:42.860
When I would come back from these excursions, I was often plunged into a kind of wonder

18:42.860 --> 18:45.020
at my vicarious depravity.

18:45.760 --> 18:51.660
This familiar that I called out of my own soul, and sent forth alone to do his good

18:51.660 --> 18:55.780
pleasure, was a being inherently malign and villainous.

18:56.340 --> 19:03.940
His every act and thought centred on self, drinking pleasure with bestial avidity from

19:03.940 --> 19:09.060
any degree of torture to another, relentless like a man of stone.

19:10.040 --> 19:16.820
Henry Jekyll stood at times aghast before the acts of Edward Hyde, but the situation

19:16.820 --> 19:22.600
was apart from ordinary laws, and insidiously relaxed the grasp of conscience.

19:22.600 --> 19:27.400
It was Hyde, after all, and Hyde alone that was guilty.

19:27.860 --> 19:29.460
Jekyll was no worse.

19:29.800 --> 19:36.000
He woke again to his good qualities, seemingly unimpaired, and he would even make haste where

19:36.000 --> 19:40.280
it was possible to undo the evil done by Hyde.

19:40.560 --> 19:44.280
And thus his conscience slumbered.

19:45.640 --> 19:51.940
Into the details of the infamy at which I was thus connived, for even now I can scarce

19:51.940 --> 19:56.120
grant that I committed it, I have no design of entering.

19:56.880 --> 20:04.060
I mean to point out the warnings and the successive steps with which my chastisement approached.

20:04.940 --> 20:11.920
I met with one accident, which, as it brought on no consequence, I shall no more than mention.

20:13.080 --> 20:20.640
An act of cruelty to a child aroused against me the anger of a passer-by, whom I recognized

20:20.640 --> 20:23.160
the other day in the person of your kinsman.

20:23.600 --> 20:26.480
The doctor and the child's family joined him.

20:26.960 --> 20:32.780
There were moments when I feared for my life, and at last, in order to pacify their too

20:32.780 --> 20:39.160
just resentment, Edward Hyde had to bring them to the door, and pay them in a cheque

20:39.160 --> 20:41.080
drawn in the name of Henry Jekyll.

20:42.040 --> 20:47.820
But this danger was easily eliminated from the future by opening an account at another

20:47.820 --> 20:55.100
name of Edward Hyde himself, and when, by sloping my hand backward, I had supplied my

20:55.100 --> 21:00.160
double with a signature, I thought I sat beyond the reach of fate.

21:01.560 --> 21:08.420
Some two months before the murder of Sir Danvers, I had been out for one of my adventures, had

21:08.420 --> 21:14.700
returned at a late hour, and woke the next day in bed with somewhat odd sensations.

21:14.700 --> 21:22.240
It was in vain I looked about me, in vain I saw the decent furniture and tall proportions

21:22.240 --> 21:29.500
of my room in the square, in vain that I recognized a pattern of the bed-curtains, and the design

21:29.500 --> 21:35.800
of the mahogany frame, something still kept insisting that I was not where I was, that

21:35.800 --> 21:42.520
I had not wakened where I seemed to be, but in the little room in Soho, where I was accustomed

21:42.520 --> 21:45.060
to sleep in the body of Edward Hyde.

21:46.040 --> 21:53.820
I smiled to myself, and in my psychological way began lazily to inquire into the elements

21:53.820 --> 22:00.920
of this illusion, occasionally, even as I did so, dropping back into a comfortable morning

22:00.920 --> 22:01.720
doze.

22:02.820 --> 22:10.380
I was still so engaged when, in one of my more wakeful moments, my eyes fell upon my

22:10.380 --> 22:10.960
hand.

22:12.160 --> 22:19.060
Now, the hand of Henry Jekyll, as you have often remarked, was professional in shape

22:19.060 --> 22:24.040
and size, it was large, firm, white, and comely.

22:24.740 --> 22:31.260
But the hand which I now saw, clearly enough in the yellow light of a mid-London morning,

22:31.820 --> 22:40.180
lying half shut on the bed-clothes, was lean, cordy, knuckly, of a dusky pallor, and thickly

22:40.180 --> 22:42.580
shaded with a swart growth of hair.

22:43.400 --> 22:46.800
It was the hand of Edward Hyde.

22:48.440 --> 22:53.840
I must have stared upon it for near half a minute, sunk as I was in the mere stupidity

22:53.840 --> 23:01.200
of wonder, before terror woke up in my breast as sudden and startling as the crash of cymbals,

23:01.460 --> 23:05.160
and bounding from my bed I rushed to the mirror.

23:05.840 --> 23:13.800
At the sight that met my eyes, my blood was changed into something exquisitely thin and

23:13.800 --> 23:14.220
icy.

23:15.640 --> 23:19.680
Yes, I had gone to bed Henry Jekyll.

23:20.260 --> 23:23.160
I had awakened Edward Hyde.

23:24.360 --> 23:26.540
How was this to be explained?

23:26.620 --> 23:27.760
I asked myself.

23:28.200 --> 23:32.800
And then, with another bound of terror, how was it to be remedied?

23:32.800 --> 23:39.560
It was well on in the morning, the servants were up, all my drugs were in the cabinet,

23:40.060 --> 23:46.480
a long journey down two pairs of stairs, through the back passage, across the open courts,

23:46.500 --> 23:52.500
and through the anatomical theatre, from where I was then standing horror-struck.

23:54.160 --> 24:01.080
It might indeed be possible to cover my face, but of what use was that, when I was unable

24:01.080 --> 24:03.940
to conceal the alteration in my stature?

24:04.840 --> 24:12.060
And then, with an overpowering sweetness of relief, it came back upon my mind that the

24:12.060 --> 24:15.800
servants were already used to the coming and going of my second self.

24:16.920 --> 24:23.660
I had soon dressed, as well as I was able, in clothes of my own size, had soon passed

24:23.660 --> 24:29.920
through the house, where Bradshaw stared and drew back at seeing Mr. Hyde at such an hour,

24:29.920 --> 24:36.680
and in such a strange array, and ten minutes later Dr. Jekyll had returned to his own

24:36.680 --> 24:43.260
shape and was sitting down, with a darkened brow, to make a faint of breakfasting.

24:45.520 --> 24:47.820
Small indeed was my appetite.

24:48.200 --> 24:59.900
This inexplicable incident, this reversal of my previous experience, seemed like the

24:59.900 --> 25:06.780
judgment, and I began to reflect more seriously than ever before on the issues and possibilities

25:06.780 --> 25:08.500
of my double existence.

25:09.460 --> 25:16.180
That part of me which I had the power of projecting, had lately been much exercised and nourished.

25:16.400 --> 25:22.380
It had seemed to me of late, as though the body of Edward Hyde had grown in stature,

25:22.800 --> 25:29.340
as though, before I wore that form, I were conscious of a more generous tide of blood,

25:29.880 --> 25:36.720
and I began to spy a danger, that if this were much prolonged, the balance of my nature

25:36.720 --> 25:43.400
might be permanently overthrown, the power of voluntary change be forfeited, and the

25:43.400 --> 25:47.880
character of Edward Hyde become irrevocably mine.

25:49.780 --> 25:54.640
The power of the drug had not been always equally displayed.

25:55.700 --> 26:00.120
Once, very early in my career, it had totally failed me.

26:00.560 --> 26:06.940
Since then I had been obliged, on more than one occasion, to double, and once with infinite

26:06.940 --> 26:09.480
risk of death, to treble the amount.

26:09.480 --> 26:16.780
And these rare uncertainties had cast hitherto the sole shadow on my contentment.

26:17.880 --> 26:25.220
Now, however, and in the light of that morning's accident, I was led to remark that, whereas

26:25.220 --> 26:31.340
in the beginning the difficulty had been to throw off the body of Jekyll, it had of late

26:31.340 --> 26:36.020
gradually but decidedly transferred itself to the other side.

26:36.020 --> 26:44.960
All things therefore seemed to point to this, that I was slowly losing hold of my original

26:44.960 --> 26:52.520
and better self, and becoming slowly incorporated with my second and worse.

26:55.160 --> 26:59.400
Between these two I now felt I had to choose.

27:00.040 --> 27:06.840
My two natures had memory in common, but all other faculties were most unequally shared

27:06.840 --> 27:07.860
between them.

27:08.380 --> 27:15.300
Jekyll, who was composite, now with the most sensitive apprehensions, now with a greedy

27:15.300 --> 27:19.440
gusto projected and shared in the pleasures and adventures of Hyde.

27:20.420 --> 27:27.580
But Hyde was indifferent to Jekyll, or but remembered him as the mountain bandit remembers

27:27.580 --> 27:30.660
the cavern in which he conceals himself from pursuit.

27:31.780 --> 27:38.000
Jekyll had more than a father's interest, Hyde had more than a son's indifference.

27:39.260 --> 27:45.800
To cast him my lot with Jekyll was to die to those appetites which I had long secretly

27:45.800 --> 27:48.960
indulged and had of late begun to pamper.

27:49.800 --> 27:57.440
To cast it in with Hyde was to die to a thousand interests and aspirations, and to become at

27:57.440 --> 28:01.740
the blow and for ever despised and friendless.

28:02.680 --> 28:08.960
The bargain might appear unequal, but there was still another consideration in the scales,

28:09.680 --> 28:15.800
for while Jekyll would suffer smartingly in the fires of abstinence, Hyde would not even

28:15.800 --> 28:17.940
be conscious of all that he had lost.

28:18.720 --> 28:25.560
Strange as my circumstances were, the terms of this debate are as old and commonplace

28:25.560 --> 28:26.400
as man.

28:26.400 --> 28:32.480
Much the same inducements and alarms cast the die for any tempted and trembling sinner,

28:32.980 --> 28:40.320
and it fell out with me as it falls with so vast a majority of my fellows, that I chose

28:40.320 --> 28:45.980
the better part, and was found wanting in the strength to keep to it.

28:46.820 --> 28:53.780
Yes I preferred the elderly and discontented doctor, surrounded by friends and cherishing

28:53.780 --> 29:00.600
honest hopes, and bade a resolute farewell to the liberty, the comparative youth, the

29:00.600 --> 29:07.740
light step, leaping impulses, and secret pleasures that I had enjoyed in the disguise of Hyde.

29:08.720 --> 29:15.260
I made this choice perhaps with some unconscious reservation, for I never gave up the house

29:15.260 --> 29:21.840
in Zoho, nor destroyed the clothes of Edward Hyde, which still lay ready in my cabinet.

29:22.620 --> 29:27.740
For two months, however, I was true to my determination.

29:28.520 --> 29:35.100
For two months I led a life of such severity as I had never before attained to, and enjoyed

29:35.100 --> 29:37.880
the compensations of an approving conscience.

29:39.000 --> 29:43.780
But time began at last to obliterate the freshness of my alarm.

29:44.140 --> 29:48.120
The praises of conscience began to grow into a thing of course.

29:48.610 --> 29:56.260
I began to be tortured with throws and longings, as of Hyde struggling after freedom, and at

29:56.260 --> 30:03.620
last, in an hour of moral weakness, I once again compounded and swallowed the transforming

30:03.620 --> 30:04.440
draught.

30:07.360 --> 30:13.540
I do not suppose that, when a drunkard reasons with himself upon his vice, he is once out

30:14.300 --> 30:20.400
times affected by the dangers that he runs through his brutish physical insensibility.

30:21.440 --> 30:27.020
Neither had I, long as I had considered my position, made enough allowance for the complete

30:27.020 --> 30:33.680
moral insensibility and insensate readiness to evil, which were the leading carriages

30:33.680 --> 30:35.300
of Edward Hyde.

30:36.120 --> 30:39.680
Yet it was by these that I was punished.

30:40.640 --> 30:43.720
My devil had long been caged.

30:44.280 --> 30:46.100
He came out roaring.

30:47.020 --> 30:53.800
I was conscious, even when I took the draught, of a more unbridled, more furious propensity

30:53.800 --> 30:54.500
to ill.

30:55.020 --> 31:01.560
It must have been this, I suppose, that stirred in my soul that tempest of impatience with

31:01.560 --> 31:05.420
which I listened to the civilities of my unhappy victim.

31:06.290 --> 31:14.120
I declare, at least, before God, no man morally sane could have been guilty of that crime

31:14.120 --> 31:20.440
upon so pitiful a provocation, and that I struck in no more reasonable spirit than that

31:20.440 --> 31:22.920
in which a sick child may break a plaything.

31:23.800 --> 31:30.760
But I had voluntarily stripped myself of all those balancing instincts by which even the

31:30.760 --> 31:38.340
of us continues to walk with some degree of steadiness among temptations, and in my case

31:38.340 --> 31:43.020
to be tempted, however slightly, was to fall.

31:44.380 --> 31:48.400
Instantly the spirit of hell awoke in me enraged.

31:48.700 --> 31:57.000
With a transport of glee I mauled the unresisting body, tasting delight from every blow, and

31:57.000 --> 32:03.300
it was not till weariness had begun to succeed that I was suddenly, in the top fit of my

32:03.300 --> 32:07.660
delirium, struck through the heart by a cold thrill of terror.

32:08.840 --> 32:10.640
A mist dispersed.

32:10.980 --> 32:18.520
I saw my life to be forfeit, and fled from the scene of these excesses, at once glorying

32:18.520 --> 32:26.320
and trembling, my lust of evil gratified and stimulated, my love of life screwed to the

32:26.320 --> 32:27.400
utmost peg.

32:28.620 --> 32:35.740
I ran to the house in Soho, and, to make assurance doubly sure, destroyed my papers.

32:36.620 --> 32:42.940
Hence I set out through the lamplit streets, in the same divided ecstasy of mind, gloating

32:42.940 --> 32:49.340
on my crime, light-headedly devising others in the future, and yet still hastening and

32:49.340 --> 32:52.440
still harkening in my wake for the steps of the Avenger.

32:53.180 --> 33:00.440
Hyde had a song upon his lips as he compounded the draught, and as he drank it pledged the

33:00.440 --> 33:01.240
dead man.

33:02.480 --> 33:09.740
The pangs of transformation had not done tearing him, before Henry Jekyll, with streaming tears

33:09.740 --> 33:15.900
of gratitude and remorse, had fallen upon his knees and lifted his clasped hands to

33:15.900 --> 33:16.260
God.

33:17.080 --> 33:22.060
The veil of self-indulgence was rent from head to foot.

33:22.700 --> 33:25.040
I saw my life as a whole.

33:25.700 --> 33:31.900
I followed it up from the days of my childhood, when I had walked with my father's hand, and

33:31.900 --> 33:39.060
through the self-denying toils of my professional life, to arrive again and again with the same

33:39.060 --> 33:43.120
sense of unreality at the damned horrors of the evening.

33:43.980 --> 33:46.780
I could have screamed aloud.

33:47.000 --> 33:53.120
I sought with tears and prayers to smother down the crowd of hideous images and sounds,

33:53.620 --> 34:00.920
with which my memory swarmed against me, and still, between the petitions, the ugly face

34:00.920 --> 34:04.000
of my iniquity stared into my soul.

34:04.840 --> 34:12.540
As the acuteness of this remorse began to die away, it was succeeded by a sense of joy.

34:13.340 --> 34:16.580
The problem of my conduct was solved.

34:17.400 --> 34:20.020
Hide was thenceforth impossible.

34:20.780 --> 34:26.360
Whether I would or not, I was now confined to the better part of my existence.

34:27.140 --> 34:31.240
And, oh, how I rejoiced to think of it!

34:31.500 --> 34:37.060
With what willing humility I embraced and knew the restrictions of natural life!

34:37.620 --> 34:44.320
With what sincere renunciation I locked the door by which I had so often gone and come,

34:44.960 --> 34:47.680
and ground the key under my heel!

34:50.080 --> 34:56.440
The next day came the news that the murder had not been overlooked, that the guilt of

34:56.440 --> 35:02.460
hide was patent to the world, and that the victim was a man high in public estimation.

35:03.020 --> 35:07.580
It was not only a crime, it had been a tragic folly.

35:08.600 --> 35:11.340
I think I was glad to know it.

35:11.520 --> 35:16.880
I think I was glad to have my better impulses thus buttressed and guarded by the terrors

35:16.880 --> 35:17.640
of the scaffold.

35:18.720 --> 35:21.720
Jekyll was now my city of refuge.

35:22.660 --> 35:29.560
Let but hide peep out an instant, and the hands of all men would be raised to take and

35:29.560 --> 35:30.280
slay him.

35:31.700 --> 35:36.380
I resolved in my future conduct to redeem the past.

35:37.000 --> 35:42.020
And I can say with honesty that my resolve was fruitful of some good.

35:42.020 --> 35:49.020
You know yourself how earnestly, in the last days of the last year, I laboured to relieve

35:49.020 --> 35:49.660
suffering.

35:50.280 --> 35:57.020
You know that much was done for others, and that the days passed quietly, almost happily

35:57.020 --> 35:58.040
for myself.

35:58.940 --> 36:03.720
Nor can I truly say that I wearied of this beneficent and innocent life.

36:04.340 --> 36:09.060
I think instead that I daily enjoyed it more completely.

36:09.060 --> 36:16.640
But I was still cursed with my duality of purpose, and as the first edge of my penitence

36:16.640 --> 36:26.480
wore off, the lower side of me, so long indulged, so recently chained down, began to growl for

36:26.480 --> 36:27.020
license.

36:27.800 --> 36:30.400
Not that I dreamed of resuscitating hide.

36:30.900 --> 36:34.740
The bare idea of that would startle me to frenzy.

36:35.380 --> 36:41.320
No, it was in my own person that I was once more tempted to trifle with my conscience,

36:41.900 --> 36:49.720
and it was as an ordinary secret sinner that I at last fell before the assaults of temptation.

36:51.520 --> 36:54.960
There comes an end to all things.

36:55.660 --> 37:03.420
The most capacious measure is filled at last, and this brief condescension to my evil finally

37:03.420 --> 37:06.260
destroyed the balance of my soul.

37:07.400 --> 37:09.820
And yet I was not alarmed.

37:10.300 --> 37:16.100
The fall seemed natural, like a return to the old days before I had made my discovery.

37:16.900 --> 37:24.200
It was a fine, clear January day, wet underfoot, where the frost had melted, but cloudless

37:24.200 --> 37:24.800
overhead.

37:25.980 --> 37:31.400
And the Regent's Park was full of winter churrupings, and sweet with spring odours.

37:32.200 --> 37:40.340
I sat in the sun on a bench, the animal within me licking the chops of memory, the spiritual

37:40.340 --> 37:47.140
side a little drowsed, promising subsequent penitence, but not yet moved to begin.

37:47.960 --> 37:56.000
After all, I reflected, I was like my neighbours, and then I smiled, comparing myself with other

37:56.000 --> 38:03.120
men, comparing my active goodwill with the lazy cruelty of their neglect, and at the

38:03.120 --> 38:10.640
very moment of that vain glorious thought a qualm came over me, a horrid nausea, and

38:10.640 --> 38:12.840
the most deadly shuddering.

38:14.340 --> 38:23.040
These passed away and left me faint, and then as in its turn faintness subsided.

38:24.320 --> 38:31.340
I began to be aware of a change in the temper of my thoughts, a greater boldness, a contempt

38:31.340 --> 38:36.080
of danger, a solution of the bonds of obligation.

38:36.920 --> 38:38.320
I looked down.

38:39.200 --> 38:46.160
My clothes hung formlessly on my shrunken limbs, the hand that lay on my knee was corded

38:46.160 --> 38:46.820
and hairy.

38:47.580 --> 38:51.120
I was once more Edward Hyde.

38:52.100 --> 38:58.500
A moment before I had been safe of all men's respect, wealthy, beloved, the cloth laying

38:58.500 --> 39:06.400
from me in the dining-room at home, and now I was the common quarry of mankind, hunted,

39:06.840 --> 39:10.760
homeless, a known murderer, thrall to the gallows.

39:12.020 --> 39:16.260
My reason wavered, but it did not fail me utterly.

39:16.720 --> 39:23.460
I have more than once observed that in my second character my faculties seemed sharpened

39:23.460 --> 39:27.400
to a point, and my spirits more tensely elastic.

39:28.300 --> 39:35.000
Thus it came about that, where Jekyll perhaps might have succumbed, Hyde rose to the importance

39:35.000 --> 39:35.800
of the moment.

39:36.700 --> 39:40.240
My drugs were in one of the presses of my cabinet.

39:40.920 --> 39:42.880
How was I to reach them?

39:42.880 --> 39:49.940
That was the problem that, crushing my temples in my hands, I set myself to solve.

39:51.160 --> 39:53.360
The laboratory door I had closed.

39:53.920 --> 39:59.560
If I sought to enter by the house, my own servants would consign me to the gallows.

40:00.280 --> 40:05.320
I saw I must employ another hand, and thought of Lanyon.

40:06.040 --> 40:07.720
How was he to be reached?

40:07.820 --> 40:08.700
How persuaded?

40:09.340 --> 40:15.200
Supposing that I escaped capture in the streets, how was I to make my way into his presence?

40:15.880 --> 40:23.060
How should I, an unknown and displeasing visitor, prevail on the famous physician to rifle the

40:23.060 --> 40:25.480
study of his colleague Dr. Jekyll?

40:27.080 --> 40:33.340
Then I remembered that of my original character one part remained to me.

40:33.760 --> 40:41.240
I could write my own hand, and once I had conceived that kindling spark, the way that

40:41.240 --> 40:45.420
I must follow became lighted up from end to end.

40:46.840 --> 40:53.160
Thereupon I arranged my clothes as best I could, and summoning a passing handsome, drove

40:53.160 --> 40:58.460
to an hotel in Portland Street, the name of which I chanced to remember.

40:59.340 --> 41:05.220
At my appearance, which was indeed comical enough, however tragic a fate these garments

41:05.220 --> 41:09.040
covered, the driver could not conceal his mirth.

41:09.420 --> 41:15.660
I gnashed my teeth upon him with a gust of devilish fury, and the smile withered from

41:15.660 --> 41:16.560
his face.

41:17.100 --> 41:24.140
Happily for him, yet more happily for myself, for in another instant I had certainly dragged

41:24.140 --> 41:25.560
him from his perch.

41:26.480 --> 41:34.160
At the inn, as I entered, I looked about me with so black a countenance as made the attendants

41:34.160 --> 41:34.880
tremble.

41:35.760 --> 41:43.100
Not a look did they exchange in my presence, but obsequiously took my orders, led me to

41:43.100 --> 41:46.900
a private room, and brought me wherewithal to write.

41:47.940 --> 41:55.240
Hyde, in danger of his life, was a creature new to me, shaken with inordinate anger, strung

41:55.240 --> 41:59.480
to the pitch of murder, lusting to inflict pain.

42:00.480 --> 42:06.820
Yet the creature was astute, mastered his fury with a great effort of the will, composed

42:06.820 --> 42:13.960
his two important letters, one to Lanyon and one to Poole, and that he might receive actual

42:13.960 --> 42:19.380
evidence of their being posted, sent them out with directions that they should be registered.

42:20.560 --> 42:26.740
Thenceforward he sat all day over the fire in the private room, gnawing his nails.

42:27.520 --> 42:33.940
There he dined, sitting alone with his fears, the waiter visibly quailing before his eye,

42:34.300 --> 42:40.500
and thence, when the night was fully come, he set forth in the corner of a closed cab,

42:41.000 --> 42:44.560
and was driven to and fro about the streets of the city.

42:46.740 --> 42:54.600
He—I say I cannot say I—that child of hell had nothing human, nothing lived in him

42:54.600 --> 43:01.980
but fear and hatred, and when at last, thinking the driver had begun to grow suspicious, he

43:01.980 --> 43:09.140
discharged the cab and ventured on foot, attired in his misfitting clothes, an object marked

43:09.140 --> 43:16.740
for observation, into the midst of the nocturnal passengers, these two base passions raged

43:16.740 --> 43:18.660
within him like a tempest.

43:19.680 --> 43:26.160
He walked fast, hunted by his fears, chattering to himself, skulking through the less frequented

43:26.160 --> 43:30.920
thoroughfares, counting the minutes that still divided him from midnight.

43:31.900 --> 43:35.780
Once a woman spoke to him, offering, I think, a box of lights.

43:35.780 --> 43:40.280
He smote her in the face, and she fled.

43:41.780 --> 43:49.000
When I came to myself at Lanyon's, the horror of my old friend perhaps affected me somewhat.

43:49.820 --> 43:51.160
I do not know.

43:51.800 --> 43:56.620
It was at least but a drop in the sea to the abhorrence with which I looked back upon these

43:56.620 --> 43:57.100
hours.

43:57.940 --> 43:59.740
A change had come over me.

43:59.740 --> 44:02.740
It was no longer the fear of the gallows.

44:03.140 --> 44:06.560
It was the horror of being hide that wracked me.

44:07.160 --> 44:11.280
I received Lanyon's condemnation partly in a dream.

44:11.880 --> 44:16.220
It was partly in a dream that I came home to my own house and got into bed.

44:17.160 --> 44:24.520
I slept after the prostration of the day with a stringent and profound slumber, which not

44:24.520 --> 44:27.840
even the nightmares that wrung me could avail to break.

44:28.760 --> 44:33.500
I woke in the morning shaken, weakened, but refreshed.

44:34.080 --> 44:39.580
I still hated and feared the thought of the brute that slept within me.

44:40.140 --> 44:46.480
And I had not, of course, forgotten the apolic dangers of the day before, but I was once

44:46.480 --> 44:54.000
more at home, in my own house, and close to my drugs, and gratitude for my escape, shone

44:54.000 --> 44:58.860
so strong in my soul that it almost rivaled the brightness of hope.

45:00.340 --> 45:06.140
I was stepping leisurely across the court after breakfast, drinking the chill of the

45:06.140 --> 45:13.920
air with pleasure, when I was seized again with those indescribable sensations that heralded

45:13.920 --> 45:14.740
the change.

45:15.400 --> 45:21.460
And I had but the time to gain the shelter of my cabinet before I was once again raging

45:21.460 --> 45:24.220
and freezing with the passions of hide.

45:25.540 --> 45:34.300
It took on this occasion a double dose to recall me to myself, and, alas, six hours

45:34.300 --> 45:41.980
after, as I sat looking sadly in the fire, the pangs returned, and the drug had to be

45:41.980 --> 45:42.640
re-administered.

45:43.620 --> 45:51.380
In short, from that day forth it seemed only by great effort as of gymnastics, and only

45:51.380 --> 45:57.120
under the immediate stimulation of the drug, that I was able to wear the countenance of

45:57.120 --> 45:57.580
juggle.

45:58.520 --> 46:04.680
At all hours of the day and night I would be taken with a premonitory shudder.

46:04.920 --> 46:12.020
Above all, if I slept, or even dozed for a moment in my chair, it was always as hide

46:12.020 --> 46:13.180
that I awakened.

46:14.240 --> 46:20.740
Under the strain of this continually impending doom, and by the sleeplessness to which I

46:20.740 --> 46:28.520
now condemned myself, ay, even beyond what I had thought possible to man, I became in

46:28.520 --> 46:37.540
my own person a creature eaten up and emptied by fever, languidly weak both in body and

46:37.540 --> 46:43.580
mind, and solely occupied by one thought of my other self.

46:44.560 --> 46:51.920
But when I slept, or when the virtue of the medicine wore off, I would leap almost without

46:51.920 --> 46:57.900
transition, for the pangs of transformation grew daily less marked, into the possession

46:57.900 --> 47:05.060
of a fancy brimming with images of terror, a soul boiling with causeless hatreds, and

47:05.060 --> 47:10.400
a body that seemed not strong enough to contain the raging energies of life.

47:11.230 --> 47:18.360
The powers of hide seemed to have grown with the sickliness of juggle, and certainly the

47:18.360 --> 47:22.120
hate that now divided them was equal on each side.

47:22.560 --> 47:25.620
With juggle it was a thing of vital instinct.

47:26.060 --> 47:31.800
He now had seen the full deformity of that creature that shared with him some of the

47:31.800 --> 47:38.840
phenomena of consciousness, and was co-heir with him to death, and beyond these links

47:38.840 --> 47:44.380
of community, which in themselves made the most poignant part of his distress, he thought

47:44.380 --> 47:51.960
of hide, for all his energy of life, as of something not only hellish, but inorganic.

47:52.780 --> 47:59.060
This was the shocking thing, that the slime of the pit seemed to utter cries and voices,

47:59.660 --> 48:07.280
that the amorphous dust gesticulated and sinned, that what was dead and had no shape should

48:07.280 --> 48:10.140
usurp the offices of life.

48:11.200 --> 48:19.220
And this again, that that insurgent horror was knit to him closer than a wife, closer

48:19.220 --> 48:25.460
than an eye, lay caged in his flesh, where he heard it mutter and felt it struggle to

48:25.460 --> 48:33.120
be born, and at every hour of weakness, and in the confidence of slumber, prevailed against

48:33.540 --> 48:36.320
and deposed him out of life.

48:37.800 --> 48:41.300
The hatred of hide for juggle was of a different colour.

48:42.100 --> 48:48.560
His terror of the gallows drove him continually to commit temporary suicide, and return to

48:48.560 --> 48:52.260
his subordinate station of a part instead of a person.

48:53.060 --> 48:58.840
But he loathed the necessity, he loathed the despondency into which juggle was now fallen,

48:58.840 --> 49:03.540
and he resented the dislike with which he was himself regarded.

49:04.320 --> 49:10.620
Hence the ape-like tricks that he would play me, scrawling in my own hand blasphemies on

49:10.620 --> 49:15.760
the pages of my books, burning the letters and destroying the portraits of my father,

49:16.320 --> 49:22.920
and indeed, had it not been for his fear of death, he would long ago have ruined himself

49:22.920 --> 49:25.920
in order to involve me in the ruin.

49:26.720 --> 49:30.000
But his love of me is wonderful.

49:30.560 --> 49:31.720
I go further.

49:32.260 --> 49:38.380
I, who sicken and freeze at the mere thought of him, when I recall the abjection and passion

49:38.380 --> 49:44.100
of this attachment, and when I know how he fears my power to cut him off by suicide,

49:44.840 --> 49:48.440
I find it in my heart to pity him.

49:49.620 --> 49:56.520
It is useless, and the time awfully fails me, to prolong this description.

49:57.400 --> 50:00.480
No one has ever suffered such torments.

50:01.300 --> 50:10.180
Let that suffice, and yet even to these habit brought no, not alleviation, but a certain

50:10.180 --> 50:16.940
callousness of soul, a certain acquiescence of despair, and my punishment might have gone

50:16.940 --> 50:24.600
for years, but for the last calamity which has now fallen, and which has finally severed

50:24.600 --> 50:27.100
me from my own face and nature.

50:28.680 --> 50:34.600
My provision of the salts, which had never been renewed since the date of the first experiment,

50:35.260 --> 50:36.560
began to run low.

50:37.080 --> 50:40.720
I sent out for a fresh supply, and mixed the draft.

50:41.380 --> 50:44.720
The ebullition followed, and the first change of colour.

50:45.360 --> 50:46.700
Not the second.

50:47.960 --> 50:51.960
I drank it, and it was without efficiency.

50:53.500 --> 50:57.620
You will learn from Poole how I have had London ransacked.

50:58.660 --> 51:07.060
It was in vain, and I am now persuaded that my first supply was impure, and that it was

51:07.060 --> 51:12.000
that unknown impurity which lent efficacy to the draft.

51:14.680 --> 51:20.820
About a week has passed, and I am now finishing this statement under the influence of the

51:20.820 --> 51:22.540
last of the old powders.

51:23.500 --> 51:31.180
This then is the last time, short of a miracle, that Henry Jekyll can think his own thoughts,

51:31.180 --> 51:32.980
or see his own face.

51:33.620 --> 51:36.980
Now how sadly altered! in the glass!

51:37.820 --> 51:44.260
Nor must I delay too long to bring my writing to an end, for if my narrative has hitherto

51:44.260 --> 51:50.840
escape destruction, it has been by a combination of great prudence and great good luck.

51:51.520 --> 51:57.260
Should the throes of change take me in the act of writing it, I will tear it in pieces.

51:57.980 --> 52:04.460
But if some time shall have elapsed after I have laid it by, his wonderful selfishness

52:04.460 --> 52:10.460
and circumscription to the moment will probably save it once again from the action of his

52:10.460 --> 52:11.760
ape-like spite.

52:13.020 --> 52:19.680
And indeed the doom that is closing on us both has already changed and crushed him.

52:20.240 --> 52:27.060
Half an hour from now, when I shall again and for ever re-endue that hated personality,

52:27.900 --> 52:36.360
I know how I shall sit shuddering and weeping in my chair, or continue, with the most strained

52:36.360 --> 52:43.260
and fear-struck ecstasy of listening, to pace up and down this room, my last earthly

52:43.260 --> 52:48.160
refuge, and give ear to every sound of menace.

52:49.040 --> 52:56.200
Will Hyde die upon the scaffold, or will he find courage to release himself at the last

52:56.200 --> 52:56.720
moment?

52:58.140 --> 52:59.380
God knows!

52:59.880 --> 53:01.240
I am careless.

53:02.020 --> 53:08.140
This is my true hour of death, concerns another than myself.

53:09.340 --> 53:17.320
Here then, as I lay down the pen and proceed to seal up my confession, I bring the life

53:17.320 --> 53:22.040
of that unhappy Henry Jekyll to an end.

53:24.760 --> 53:30.060
End of the strange case of Doctor Jekyll and Mr. Hyde.

